    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-19T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-19T10:00:00-05:00" n="145"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.24/405: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-19T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 19, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1004. The Swedish Minister told me this morning that in a recent conversation
                    with the Counselor of the German Embassy<note n="72" xml:id="d145fn72">Gustav
                        Hilger.</note> the latter, in referring to discussions taking place in
                    Berlin with the object of increasing Soviet deliveries to Germany had stated
                    that <pb facs="0157" n="145" xml:id="pg_145"/> what Germany desired was a
                    substantial increase in deliveries of grain, oils and what he described as
                    “minerals”. He had also remarked that an exchange or barter basis between the
                    Soviet Union and Germany was no longer possible and that the Soviet Government
                    would now have to extend credit to Germany.<note n="73" xml:id="d145fn73"
                        >Further details on these economic relations are printed in <hi
                            rend="italic">Nazi-Soviet Relations, 1939–1941</hi>, pp. 318–346, <hi
                            rend="italic">passim</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
